@NODE O. "Some Features that ZoolDIZ offers"

 - @{b}Full 3l173 (ELITE ;)) capability if necessary... [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_elite.IFF"}]@{ub}

    * @{"SentBy" Link D.} line with color values!
    * upto 100 lines in description

 - @{b}Q-Dizolve Compability@{ub}

    * >8 line descs will be stored at the same directory
    * Possible @{"signatures" Link D.} will be automatically converted to ZoolDIZ-Form!

 - @{b}Compact mode@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_normal.IFF"}]@{ub}

    * Forces you to select lines to be used from description

 - @{b}Automatic Mode@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_elite.IFF"}]@{ub}

    * If ZoolDIZ founds or creates a description, it's possible to fill out
      the description without even one keypress!

 - @{b}The best ModuleHandling routine ever seen / made@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_mod.IFF"}]

    * Works with both unpacked as well as packed modules 

      - Archived ones: LHA/LZX/ZIP
      - XPK and PowerPacker packed

    * Supports various formats:

      - ProTracker modules (And compatibles)
      - MultiChannel modules: S3M/XM/MTM/68CHNL @{"Hi Pauli!" Link 5.}
      - PlaySID modules

 - @{b}100% full support to mp1, mp2 & mp3 files!@{ub}
 
    * No more fuzzed up mpeg audio areas! All files will be in clean order
      and have standard MPEG-AUDIO-TAG attached to them!

 - @{b}Full support to PowerPacker & XPK packed files@{ub}

    * Every format can be packed with XPK or PowerPacker (Should be avoided)

      - Even a XPK packed LHA archive with a module inside would work!
      - Extremely handy to have around if you need to adopt your own modules

 - @{b}Handles JPG/GIF/IFF pictures easily@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_pics.IFF"}]

    * Creates description in: 320x256x24 form

 - @{b}Has got Three (3) different editors to maximize easy usage:@{ub}

    * Normal Editor, Module Description editor & Picture Desc. editor

 - @{b}Does not require FILE.ID.DIZ type description@{ub}

    * ZoolDIZ is capable to extract descriptions out from AMiNET-Files @{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_aminet.IFF"}]

      - Perfect for CD-ROMS
      - Ideal for Aminet exports
      - Will scan the archive itself for the readme as well as the external one!

    * Various internal scans for Modules / Textfiles!

 - @{b}Full Aminetheader capabitilities@{ub}

    * "ZoolDIZ.AMiNETHEADERS" contains various headers which will be added
      to a file which had a aminet-description

      - You can use the sample ones or add your own!

    * Isn't necessary, so it can be turned off too

 - @{b}Does not allow MCI bombs...@{ub}

    * It will not bypass any MCI command characters

 - @{b}Works 100% with multinode systems...@{ub}

    * Every port has got it's own directory that will be deleted after use!

 - @{b}ZoolDIZ will allow packed TEXT-Files in LHA/LZX archives (if the archive
   is less than 25kb)@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_dubbel.IFF"}]

    * The biggest file will be handled just like unpacked file

 - @{b}There's possibility to strip all unwanted lines from description@{ub}
   
    * External file called ZoolDIZ.STRIP will be used

 - @{b}Visual type Configuration editor to make configfile creation or editing
   a piece of cake! [@{"Hi PMK" Link 5.}]@{ub} [@{"SCREENSHOT " system "VT HI LA screenshots/ZoolDIZ_config.IFF"}]@{ub}

    * Just like CNets own editors (Edit Account etc.)

 - @{b}Full Virus Scanning option (Uses Virus Checker or VirusZ II)@{ub}
   
    * All unpacked files & LHA/LZX packed files will be checked, WHEN the
      uploader logs off... this way we and the user will save online time

    * The VirusScanner is a normal ARexx-script, so you can add it to the
      maintenance if you like

 - @{b}And yet more to come...@{ub}

@ENDNODE

