@NODE 1. "Introduction to the world of ZooLDIZ 2"


ZoolDIZ is the most powerful and efficent @{"File_ID.Diz" Link D.} processor known in modem
world. It handles all files automatically (If sysop wants so), and is designed
especially  to work  with multinode  systems. Development  is always  UpToDate,
because ZoolDIZ has got many betatesters in Helsinki, Finland near the author.

ZoolDIZ has been developed, keeping in mind, users & sysops own needs and easy
to use. ZoolDIZs most powerful option  is to  describe all files, without even
ONE  keypress! All  runs automatic  (Unless SysOP wants  users to select lines
to be used from @{"DIZ" Link D.}).

    @{b}I asked opinions through CNets own vote-door, and look at these outstanding
    results!:

    @{u}>20% I couldn't use ANYTHING ELSE!@{uu}
     30% I'm in love with ZOOLDIZ!
     30% I LIKE IT; But do not love it.@{ub}

    (And this questionaire was made in the early states of the development!)

 Here is some Information, why to use ZoolDIZ and answers to your questions..:

  @{b}a. What is ZoolDIZ?@{ub}

   - ZoolDIZ is a really good @{"Dizzer" Link D.}.

  @{b}b. Theres Q-Dizolve, and other @{"dizzers" Link D.}.. why to use ZoolDIZ, instead others?@{ub}

   - Because ZoolDIZ is so filled with useful options,  that no dizzer can get
     Even close to the ultimate ZooLDIZ!

  @{b}c. hah, hah! that's what you say! Gimme some specs!@{ub}

   - OK!, You asked for it!

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1.  First, ZoolDIZ supports various formats:

  * JPEG   Images : Will search Size & Color data, and add it to desc!
  * GIF    Images : Will search Size & Color data, and add it to desc!
  * IFF    Images : Will search Size & Color data, and add it to desc!

  * DMS  Archives : Seeks ordinary description (plain file_id.diz)
  * LHA  Archives : Seeks ordinary description + module & readme scan)
  * LZX  Archives : Seeks ordinary description + module & readme scan)
  * ZIP  Archives : Seeks ordinary description + module scan)
  * ARJ  Archives : Seeks ordinary description (plain file_id.diz)

  * TEXT    files : Seeks the desc. from: TXT, DOC, DOX, DOK & NFO files

  * Amiga    exes : Seeks ordinary description...

  * Modules       : S3M/XM/MTM/6&8Ch/PlaySID

    - Will scan them for author, full name & Channel specifications!

                    MultiChannel: [xxch] Name.......................(Author)
                    PlaySID     : [SID] Name.......................(Author)
                    ProTracker  : [MOD] Name.......................(Author)

    - All formats can be -LHA/LZX/ZIP- archived or packed with -XPK or PP-!

  * Full mp1, mp2 & mp3 support!!
  
    - [MP3] Test Song...................(Test Artist)

       Album: Test Album (1998)
       Time.: 02:18
       Type.: 128 kbit/s 44.100 kHz

2.  Full XPK / PowerPacker / LHA / LZX / ZIP support

3.  ZooLDIZ has got  it's own description editors  to help users  to  describe
    files easier....!

4.  If ZoolDIZ does not found description it will try to create it on its own!

5.  Supports different language files! (not in the demo-version)

6.  @{u}It even supports AMINET - README FILES, AND WILL SEEK IT FOR SHORT-DESC@{uu}!

And this is not all, but I would go nuts, if I'd list them all !

Look at here to see @{"more features that ZoolDIZ offers" Link O.}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------      

  d. @{b}WOW, I'm Impressed!  I do not need to ask anything anymore. I'll just
     go, and install ZoolDIZ!@{ub}

   - That's what I expected... ANd remember... If you need a option etc., just 
     contact the author, and he will help you!

ZoolDIZ-II -is- DevelWARE - You must follow the @{"rules" Link 9.}!

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "ZoolDIZ installation"

@{b}The installation part in ZoolDIZ is easy just follow the steps: @{ub}

@{i}@{u}@{b}1st step@{ui}@{ub}@{uu}: If you're using other dizzers, then remove them immediately! Other
          dizzers will cause ZoolDIZ to malfunction, because they will share the
          same resources!

@{i}@{u}@{b}2nd step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: @{fg shine}Run the Installer script by clicking it from the WorkBench!@{fg text}

@{i}@{u}@{b}3rd step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: Add the ZoolDIZ/ZoolCon.rexx to maintenance files as ARexx doors

@{i}@{u}@{b}4th step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: Configure ZoolDIZ by executing the ZoolCon.rexx

@{i}@{u}@{b}5th step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: Run the Install-BBSMenu & Install-BBSText files!

Now ZoolDIZ is ready to use. You also should performs the extra steps below:

--> Extra steps!

@{i}@{u}@{b}7th step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: If you like to use the SentBy / Signature Feature then add

 @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zooldiz/checkit.rexx} to sys.welcome

@{i}@{u}@{b}8th step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: If you need external languages (German/Swedish etc.) you can add
          them by editing ZoolDIZ.LANGUAGE(X) files:

    - The (X) means the number of language used (Check the CNet manual, if
      you don't understand!)

    - ZoolDIZ has got two default languages:

     0 = English &
     1 = Suomi (Finnish ;))

   - If you like to create your own, the instructions are in the corresponding
     files... When you're done editing your language files, then send them to
     the @{"author" Link 4.}... (especially looking for German)

@{i}@{u}@{b}9th step@{ui}@{uu}@{ub}: If you like to use Unwanted line-Stripping then@{uu}:

    - Create or edit "Pfiles:ZoolDIZ/ZoolDIZ.STRIP" in text-editor!
    - Enable stripping from the ConfigEditor

    Example:

    - if this string is in the "Pfiles:ZoolDIZ/ZoolDIZ.STRIP" file:
 
      "from ZIPPO"

    - and this string in DIZ:

      "downloaded from zippo"

     then the whole line will be stripped off!

@{" if you like to install the BBSText by hand, click here! " Link IN2}
@{" if you like to install the BBSMenu by hand, click here! " Link IN3}

@ENDNODE

@NODE IN2 "ZoolDIZ Installation: BBSText"

 @{fg shine}Then load BBSText into your texteditor and@{fg text}:
    
     This to the end of line 61:

        @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#1 pfiles:ZoolDIZ/ZoolDIZ.VIRUS2.rexx}

     Add into start of line 99:

        @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:ZoolDIZ/EdBack3.rexx}

     and this into END of line 99:

        @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}$0 run rx pfiles:ZoolDIZ/ZoolDIZ.VIRUS.rexx >NIL:}

        @{fg shine}@{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you like, you do not need to add the "ZoolDIZ.VIRUS.rexx"
                  to line 99.. it's normal AREXX script, so you can place it
                  to maintenance or anywhere you want!@{fg text}

     Change line 499 like this:

        @{b}[CTRL+Y]@{ub}q1@{b}[CTRL+Y]@{ub}n1@{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zooldiz/ZOOLDIZ.rexx}

     Add into start of line 465:

        @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:ZoolDIZ/LONG.rexx}

     Change line 586 like this:

        @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:ZOOLDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}@{b}[CTRL+Y]@{ub}n1Go to send files, ^X aborts@{b}[CTRL+Y]@{ub}n1

     Change line 978 like this:

        @{b}[CTRL+Y]@{ub}n2@{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:ZoolDIZ/EdBack2.rexx}

@{fg shine}It is a hell lot more easier to run the BBSText-Installer - script!!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE

@NODE IN3 "ZoolDIZ Installation: BBSMenu"

c. @{fg shine}Load BBSMenu into your favourite texteditor@{fg text}...

   And modify or add these things in it....
 
     In section: 3; Main prompt

                SENTBY | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:ZoolDIZ/ZoolSGN.rexx}

     In section: 4; ud/base

        Change: AO, Adopt Orphans
            To: AO, | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zoolDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}

        Change: Upload
            To: Upload | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zoolDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}

        Change: Write
            To: Write | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zoolDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}

     In section: 5; Respond or Pass?

        Change: Write
            To: Write | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zoolDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}

     In section: 20; Browse

        Change: Write
            To: Write | @{b}[CTRL+Q]@{ub}#0 pfiles:zoolDIZ/BBSMENU.rexx}

@{fg shine}It is a hell lot more easier to run the BBSMenu-Installer - script!!@{fg text}

@ENDNODE

