@NODE 7. "Your GUIDE to take the most out of ZOOlDIZ ˋ!"

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  The most powerful option of ZoolDIZ, when compared to other @{"DIZZER" Link D.} softwares
is the flexibility of ZoolDIZ... It will always suite to your needs...

  If you like a socalled "3li73"- board, you can use @{"SENTBY" Link D.}-lines with colors,
description with 99 lines, including group logos, etc... or you can just force
users to pick by hand only few lines from  diz, to really  tell, what's inside
of the archive...

  If you are describing LHA/LZX archive, ZoolDIZ will scan the arc for possib-
le modules... if it finds  only one module, it will se, if the size of the mo-
dule  is enough of the whole  size of the archive, it will unpack it, and pre-
tend, like it was just a one unpacked module...

  ZooLDIZ will scan all unpacked modules(*) for Author NAME and module NAME...
It will add those informations as description in format:

@{b}(*) & (**)@{ub} NAME................................(AUTHOR)

  If you upload/describe modules and the package contains DiZ, then you can
ignore the whole description and jump into ZoolDIZ - modscan with button (I) !

Easy, isn't it?

  @{u}If you wan't to DELETE all signatures (SENT-BYs), then execute@{uu}:

    @{b}"DELETE_SIGNATURES.rexx"@{ub}.. as a @{u}AREXX-DOOR@{uu} it will do it for you!

  ZoolDIZ may confuse you by all it's unlisted great options... so you'll need
to  take your time with  ZoolDIZ, to master  it, and make  your Uploading  and
description writing as easy as it will be possible....

  If you want to @{u}ADOPT AMiNET CD-ROMS or similiar system@{uu}, do like this:

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(9) For ZoolDIZ testing purposes!> @{b}ao@{ub}

Adopt from which partition @{b}(0)@{ub}? 0

@{b}Pattern:@{ub} ~(*.readme)

